Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_physical_context_data(25.10)          write_physical_context_data(25.10)

Name
       write_physical_context_data  -  Writes the physical context data needed
       for timing analysis

Syntax
       write_physical_context_data

       [-help]

       <fileName>

       [-designation <name>]

       [-type <technologyName>]

       Writes the physical context data needed for timing analysis.  The  data
       that  is  being written is associated with each instance in the design,
       or module.

       The command can be used, both in Innovus and Tempus, if  Tempus  is  in
       physical-mode  and  has  the physical data in DB to use for writing out
       the LDE data.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each write_physical_context_data parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man write_physical_context_data.

       -designation <name>
              Specifies   the   Rx   layer  width  map  from  micron  to  enum
              -um:nsw{:um:nsw}.

       <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the output file.

       -type <technologyName>
              Specifies the technology name.

